msgid "Moves a post the agent can edit to the Trash, where you can restore it. Never a permanent delete."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:142
msgid "Moves a page to the Trash, where you can restore it. Never a permanent delete."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:143
msgid "Removes an allowlisted meta key and all its values from a post the agent can edit. Only allowlisted keys."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:147
msgid "Permanently removes one revision from a post's history. The live post is unchanged, but the deleted revision cannot be recovered. Requires edit access to the parent post."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:148
msgid "Permanently deletes an attachment: the file and its library entry are removed and cannot be recovered. Requires delete access to that attachment."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:149
msgid "Removes an allowlisted meta key and all its values from a term you can edit. This cannot be undone. Only allowlisted keys."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:150
msgid "Permanently deletes a comment. This bypasses the Trash and cannot be undone — use moderate-comment to trash a comment recoverably instead. Requires edit access to that comment."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:151
msgid "Creates a new user with the site default role only (never an admin or a caller-chosen role). Requires the create-users capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:152
msgid "Permanently deletes a user and reassigns their content to another user. Never deletes you or the last administrator. Requires the delete-users capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:153
msgid "Removes an allowlisted user meta key from a user the agent can edit. This cannot be undone. Auth and capability keys can never be touched."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:154
msgid "Permanently deletes a post, bypassing the Trash. This cannot be undone — use trash-post to remove a post recoverably instead. Requires delete access to that post. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:155
msgid "Permanently deletes a page, bypassing the Trash. This cannot be undone — use trash-page to remove a page recoverably instead. Requires delete access to that page. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:156
msgid "Writes a small allowlist of site settings only (name, tagline, timezone, formats, posts per page). It can never change the site URL, admin email, default role, or open registration. Requires manage-options. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:157
msgid "Permanently deletes a navigation menu and all of its items. This cannot be undone — menus have no Trash. Requires the edit-theme-options capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:158
msgid "Permanently removes one item from a navigation menu. This cannot be undone. Requires the edit-theme-options capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:159
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce product, bypassing the Trash. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:160
msgid "Permanently deletes a product variation, bypassing the Trash. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:161
msgid "Permanently removes a global product attribute taxonomy by id. This cannot be undone — all terms in the taxonomy are lost. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:162
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce order, bypassing the Trash. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:163
msgid "Permanently deletes a note from a WooCommerce order. Requires the order id and the note id. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:164
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce order refund by refund id. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:165
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce customer, which removes the underlying WordPress user. You must name another user to inherit their content. It will not delete you or the last administrator. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:170
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce coupon by id. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:171
msgid "Lists WooCommerce shipping zones with their id, name, and order. The Rest of World zone (id 0) is always present. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:172
msgid "Reads one WooCommerce shipping zone by id, including its name, order, and configured zone locations. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:175
msgid "Permanently deletes a WooCommerce shipping zone by id. The Rest of World zone (id 0) cannot be deleted. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:176
msgid "Lists the shipping methods configured in a WooCommerce shipping zone, by zone id. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:177
msgid "Reads one shipping method from a WooCommerce shipping zone by zone id and instance id, including its type, title, and enabled state. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:178
msgid "Adds a shipping method to a WooCommerce shipping zone. Provide the zone id and method type (such as flat_rate, free_shipping, or local_pickup). Returns the new method shape. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:180
msgid "Permanently removes a shipping method from a WooCommerce shipping zone by zone id and instance id. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:183
msgid "Creates a WooCommerce tax rate from a rate value, with optional country, state, name, priority, compound flag, shipping flag, order, and class slug. Returns the full rate shape. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:185
msgid "Permanently removes a WooCommerce tax rate by id. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:189
msgid "Permanently removes a WooCommerce tax class by slug. The Standard class cannot be deleted. This cannot be undone. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability. Off by default."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:190
msgid "Returns a sales summary (total sales, order count, net sales, average order value) for a date range you specify. Queries completed and processing orders only. Defaults to the current calendar month. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:191
msgid "Returns the top-selling products for a period (week, month, or year) ordered by quantity sold. Returns product id, name, and quantity only — no pricing data. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:192
msgid "Returns order counts broken down by WooCommerce status (pending, processing, on-hold, completed, cancelled, refunded, failed) and a grand total. Read-only. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:193
msgid "Returns product counts broken down by post status (publish, draft, private, pending, trash) and a total of non-trashed products. Read-only. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:194
msgid "Returns the total count of registered users on the site. Read-only. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:195
msgid "Lists all registered WooCommerce payment gateways with id, title, and enabled state. Credential and secret settings are never returned. Read-only. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:196
msgid "Reads one payment gateway by id: title, description, enabled state, order, and non-secret settings. Fields whose names contain key, secret, token, password, api, or private are always stripped before the response is sent. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:197
msgid "Returns coupon counts broken down by post status (publish, draft, private, pending, trash) and a total of active (non-trash) coupons. Read-only. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

#: includes/admin/disclosures.php:198
msgid "Updates a payment gateway by id, changing only the fields you send: enabled state, title, description, or display order. Credential and secret fields can never be written through this ability. Returns the updated gateway shape with secrets redacted. Requires the manage-WooCommerce capability."
msgstr ""

